A man has appeared in court charged with manslaughter following the death of a "wonderful" 22-year-old man in Llanelli.Police were called to a property in Robinson Street on 25 March last year, after concerns were raised for a man's welfare.Liam Rhys Morgan-Whittle died after being taken to hospital, Dyfed-Powys Police said.Jason Thomas, from Llanelli, appeared at a hearing at Llanelli Magistrates' Court on Thursday. The 39-year-old was bailed and is expected to appear at Swansea Crown Court on 1 July. 
